The Africa Network for Environment and Economic Justice (ANEEJ) is set to organise a side event at the Civil Society Forum of the World Bank and International Monetary Fund (IMF) Spring meeting scheduled for October 15-18, 2019, in Washington DC. ANEEJ is a lead organisation implementing the transparency and accountability in the recovery and management of recovered assets (MANTRA) project, supported by the British Department for International Development (DFID). Powered by RubiQube Ad Network A statement issued Tuesday in Abuja by Acting Executive Director, Leo Atakpu, said this was sequel to the approval of a slot granted ANEEJ by the World Bank Civil Society Team. The World Bank Civil Society letter made available to newsmen read in part, “We would like to inform you that the review committee found your proposal, ‘The Role of the World Bank in Facilitating Stolen Assets’ Return’, timely and interesting. Therefore, we are pleased to provide a slot for this session at the CSPF.”